laboratory_examinations.findings: Transabdominal and transvaginal examinations were performed. Uterus measures 6 cm x 4 cm x 4 cm with the endometrium measuring approximately 3 mm. No focal uterine lesion is identified. Both ovaries are normal in size with appropriate vascular waveforms identified, without evidence for torsion. There is a trace amount of free fluid in the pelvic cul-de-sac, likely physiologic. Neither kidney demonstrates hydronephrosis.
Negative results, with reference range lower limit of 0.2 mg/dL and upper limit of 1.0 mg/dL.
